    <div class="wpd-comment-text">
    <p>Very good question. And there are no possible answers that are pleasant. As long as you understand that the “sin” he’s so hard on is that which is not immediately “repented” of according to his own definition.</p>
<p>“So hard on sin” such as “unforgiveness” by his own made-up definition. In the many MANY accounts I’ve heard of those who have suffered under this teaching, that so-called sin gets a FAR harsher treatment than the sin of child abuse.</p>

