    <div id="comment-204317" class="wpd-comment-right">
    <div class="wpd-comment-header">
    <div class="wpd-comment-author ">
    <a href="http://cryingoutforjustice.blog" rel="noreferrer ugc nofollow" target="_blank">Barbara Roberts</a>
</div>
    <div class="wpd-comment-date" title="February 13, 2021 9:15 pm">
    <i class="far fa-clock" aria-hidden="true"></i>
    3 years ago
</div>
    
    
    <div class="wpd-space"></div>
    <div class="wpd-comment-link wpd-hidden">
    <span wpd-tooltip="Comment Link" wpd-tooltip-position="left"><i class="fas fa-link" aria-hidden="true" data-wpd-clipboard="https://heresthejoy.com/2021/02/how-pedophiles-are-forgiven-from-the-teachings-of-jay-adams/#comment-204317"></i></span>
</div>
</div>
    
    <div class="wpd-comment-text">
    <p>Jay Adams taught that all that is required for repentance is a verbal confession with (perhaps) 40 days of demonstrated good conduct after the confession.  How naive!  How foolish! </p>
<p>In Genesis, Joseph did not give much credit to his brothers’ verbal confession. After hearing them confess he tested them under pressure in order to see how much their characters had changed.  </p>
<p>See my latest blog post:  “Joseph tested his brothers by falsely accusing them”.</p>

</div>
